Phase - 1
✅ Checklist for a Basic Yet Effective API Gateway
Feature	Current Status	Enhancements Needed?
1️⃣ Basic Routing & Load Balancing	✅ Done (Spring Cloud Gateway)	🔹 Add circuit breaker for resilience
2️⃣ Authentication (JWT)	✅ Implemented	🔹 OAuth2 integration (future)
3️⃣ Authorization (RBAC / Roles)	✅ Implemented	🔹 Fine-grained permission control?
4️⃣ Logging Filter	✅ Done	🔹 Correlation ID for distributed tracing
5️⃣ Rate Limiting Filter	✅ Done	🔹 Use Redis-based rate limiting for scaling
6️⃣ Caching Filter	✅ Done	🔹 Per-user or per-role caching
7️⃣ Exception Handling Filter	✅ Basic handling	🔹 Global error handling with proper response codes

Phase - 2
8️⃣ Monitoring & Observability	❌ Not set up	🔹 Add Spring Boot Actuator for health checks
9️⃣ Circuit Breaker (Resilience4J)	❌ Not set up	🔹 Prevent cascading failures in microservices
🔟 API Documentation (Swagger UI)	❌ Not set up	🔹 Helps frontend teams & external consumers
1️⃣1️⃣ Request/Response Transformation	❌ Not set up	🔹 Modify request headers or response formats dynamically
1️⃣2️⃣ Service Discovery (Eureka/Consul)	❌ Not set up	🔹 For auto-detecting services instead of hardcoding URLs
1️⃣3️⃣ Security Headers & CORS	❌ Not set up	🔹 Prevent security vulnerabilities

Phase - 3
1️⃣4️⃣ WebSocket Support (Optional)	❌ Not set up	🔹 Needed for real-time services (chat, notifications)
